hopobject.body: Could I make an appointment to see ? el ezaby pharmacy hotline Flourishing in a hothouse of perpetual recession and asphyxiating religiosity, Irish new wave was vividly distinct from its equivalents in the UK and America and this is reflected in the Rats’ music. A nutty swirl of keyboards, saxophone and soft-rock guitar, Rat Trap resembled three wildly different tunes held together with glue and sticky tape; Geldof’s scatted croon on She’s So Modern and (I Never Loved) Eva Braun inhabited a halfway house between Bryan Ferry and The Ramones.
